        <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-4xl">Proof of concept - iteration two</h3>
        <p>
            <strong>Key challenge</strong><br>
            In testing, it was loud and clear there isn't enough value to the customer in the portal yet. Customers have a negative perception of car salespeople, coupled with hesistancy over sharing personal details digitally.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Approach</strong><br>
            The focus of the 2nd iteration was around building in perceived value and trying to increase trustworthiness. 
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc mb-8 ml-10">
            <li>Added in onboarding to create more perceived value, working with a content designer to ensure the flow from email to task completion was clear</li>
            <li>Push to have system integration with their stock database so we can pull in a photo of the car booked for test drive to create more excitement around the car</li>
            <li>Added time labelling onto tasks to give customers more of a sense of time saving, and increased presence of gamification</li>
            <li>Created an 'info panel' design pattern and ensuring at every stage we ask the customer for details, we use this panel to explain why we need the customer's details</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The focus of the 2nd iteration was around building in perceived value and trying to increase trustworthiness.</p>
    </div>
</section>

